Critical issue: 168 database folders have duplicate suffixes (1), (2) indicating race conditions in folder creation logic.

Root Cause: ensureDbFolder_() function may not properly handle concurrent script executions, leading to Google Drive auto-renaming folders.

Impact: 70% of databases have duplicate folders, causing confusion and potential data inconsistency.

See handoff document: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_TROUBLESHOOTING_HANDOFF.md
See audit report: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_AUDIT_REPORT.md
DriveSheetsSync: 6 Missing CSV Files - Incomplete Syncs

Critical issue: 6 database folders exist but main CSV files are missing, indicating incomplete syncs.

Root Cause: CSV export may have failed silently or files were deleted.

Impact: Data loss risk, incomplete backups.

See handoff document: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_TROUBLESHOOTING_HANDOFF.md
See audit report: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_AUDIT_REPORT.md
DriveSheetsSync: 101 Missing Archive Folders - No Version History

High priority issue: 101 database folders are missing .archive folders, preventing version history.

Root Cause: ensureArchiveFolder_() may not be called for all databases or may fail silently.

Impact: No version history for 42% of databases.

See handoff document: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_TROUBLESHOOTING_HANDOFF.md
See audit report: /Users/brianhellemn/Projects/github-production/DRIVESHEETSSYNC_AUDIT_REPORT.md
DriveSheetsSync: 274 Orphaned Files - File Management Issues

High priority issue: 274 files don't match expected patterns, including CSV files with duplicate suffixes.

Root Cause: Google Drive auto-renaming when duplicates are created, insufficient deduplication logic.

Impact: File management confusion, potential data inconsistency.
